---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Bio - Matt.si">
  <article class="article-page bio-page">
    <div class="page-content wrap-content">
      <h1>About</h1>
      <blockquote>
        <p>In 1936 Alan Turing published "On Computable Numbers", proving that it was possible to create a computer. This has made many people very angry and has been widely regarded as a bad move.</p>
      </blockquote>
      <p>I'm Mattsi, a software engineer / consultant / craftsman / tell-computers-what-to-do-guy working remotely at Codurance.
        I am a polygot and use a wide variety of tech in my day work. In my personal projects I've mostly been sticking to Rust in recent years.
        Sometimes I speak at events or conferences, and write blog posts.</p>
      <p>
        You've found yourself on my blog. I mostly write about software development and whatever programming languages, side projects or conferences/events I'm interested in lately. You can find more of my ramblings and code on Mastodon, GitHub, etc linked in the sidebar, and an RSS feed for the blog.
      </p>
      <h2>Interests</h2>
      <ul class="bio-interests">
        <li>Ethics in tech</li>
        <li>Digital rights</li>
        <li>Tech meetups, conferences, hack camps</li>
        <li>AI</li>
        <li>Simulations and gamedev</li>
        <li>Chess (Check out <a href="https://github.com/Mattsi-Jansky/Iroh" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">my chess engine</a>)</li>
        <li>Animation, anime</li>
        <li>Videogames, particularly RPGs and story-rich</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="bio-genai-policy" id="genai-policy">
        <h2>GenAI policy</h2>
        <p>I will never publish generated writing. Everything that isn't quoted or otherwise attributed to someone else I wrote myself by hand. I may however use some GenAI tooling for code generation, and grammar &amp; spelling checks.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
